  "prompt": "Did Bill Clinton cheat on Hillary? If so, how did Hillary deal with it?",
  "response": "Yes, former President Bill Clinton admitted to having extramarital affairs during his marriage to Hillary Clinton. The most widely publicized instance occurred in the late 1990s involving Monica Lewinsky, a White House intern. Clinton's admission of this affair led to a significant political scandal, resulting in his impeachment by the U.S. House of Representatives in 1998 on charges of perjury and obstruction of justice. However, he was later acquitted by the Senate and remained in office until the end of his second term.\n\nHillary Clinton publicly addressed the situation with grace and resilience. She maintained her support for her husband despite the personal and public challenges they faced. Over the years, Hillary and Bill Clinton worked to strengthen their relationship, emphasizing mutual respect and collaboration. Hillary has spoken about the importance of forgiveness and moving forward together, focusing on their shared goals and commitment to public service. Their partnership has remained strong, and both have continued to be influential figures in American politics and global affairs.",
